Description: Glazed composition scarab; pierced longitudinally; traces of engraved head and legs and on the base a maat feather, uraeus and neb sign; very worn.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Turner Bequest Excavations, Enkomi
Curator's comments: This object is marked as 1897,0401.763 but the sketch in the register has 1897,0401.762 next to it. An extra entry for a scarab was inserted in the register with no corresponding object. This has been published in Kenna 1971 as 1897,0401.762 in catalogue no. 104.
Bibliographic references: Kenna 1971 / Catalogue of the Cypriote Seals of the Bronze Age in the British Museum (No. 104) (incorrectly labelled 1897,0401.762)
Additional IDs: Miscellaneous number: 1897,0401.762 (Register has two entries for this object.)
